text: Wong Sok I (born 15 January 1993) is a Macau karateka. In 2018, she won one of the bronze medals in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia. At the 2014 Asian Games held in Incheon, South Korea, she competed in the women's kumite 55 kg event without winning a medal. She was eliminated in her first match by Mae Soriano of the Philippines. Soriano went on to win one of the bronze medals.
